text: Phoebe is a female given name. The name is feminine of the first name Phoebus. Phoebus is a name for "Apollo", and means bright. In Greek mythology, Phoebe was a Titan associated with prophecy and the moon. This was also a name of her granddaughter Artemis. A moon of Saturn has the name in honor of the Titan. The pronunciation of the name is [ fee-bee ]. This name was ranked #247 on the US Popular Names in 2021. A different spelling is Phebe. == People == * Phoebe Bridgers, American singer-songwriter * Phoebe Cates, American actress, model, and entrepreneur * Phoebe Snow, American singer, songwriter and guitarist * Phoebe Tonkin, Australian actress and singer * Phoebe Waller- Bridge, English actress, producer and writer * Phoebe Cary, American writer (1824-1871) * Phoebe Dynevor, actor == References == Category:Given names
